Title: Introduction to PHY132
Description: General information about the course, such as the setup of recitations, exams, Webassign, and more

Title: Intro to Electric Forces
Description: Introduces forces that come from two point charges, and explains the relevant electric force formula along with the vector notation

Title: Free-Body Analysis of Point Charges
Description: Prof. Hemmick goes into detail of a free-body force diagram which explains the forces between point charges.

Title: Continued Force Analysis of Point Charges
Description: Here, we continue last lecture's force analysis of point charges, ﬁnding F_total for x and y directions, and use it to ﬁnd the magnitude and direction of the electric force.

Title: Finding Symmetry in Electric Forces
Description: Prof. Hemmick does another electric force problem, but this time uses symmetry of the system to simplify it dramatically.

Title: Force From Electric Field
Description: We introduce the concept of electric ﬁeld using a force equation and revisit the simple symmetric point charge problem, but this time using electric ﬁeld.

Title: Overview-Point Charge and Electric Force and Field
Description: Prof. Hemmick does a brief overview of what we've learned so far in Electricity.
